## Lifecycle Management System

### Overview
TSFSYSTEM has a comprehensive multi-level lifecycle verification system for transactions (invoices, orders, payments, etc.). Every list view and detail view with VerifiableModel must include lifecycle controls.

### Required Components

#### 1. Lifecycle Badges (Header/List View)
```tsx
import { LifecycleBadges } from "@/components/shared/LifecycleBadges";

<LifecycleBadges
  lifecycleStatus={invoice.lifecycle_status}  // OPEN/LOCKED/VERIFIED/CONFIRMED
  currentLevel={invoice.current_verification_level}
  requiredLevels={invoice.required_levels_frozen}
  isControlled={invoice.required_levels_frozen > 0}
/>
```

**Displays**:
- Status badge (Open, Locked, Verified, Confirmed) with color coding
- Verification progress ("L1 / L3" or "No Approval Required")

#### 2. Lifecycle Actions (Detail View Header)
```tsx
import { LifecycleActions } from "@/components/shared/LifecycleActions";

<LifecycleActions
  model="Invoice"
  instanceId={invoice.id}
  transactionType="SALES_INVOICE"
  lifecycleStatus={invoice.lifecycle_status}
  currentLevel={invoice.current_verification_level}
  requiredLevels={invoice.required_levels_frozen}
  allowOverride={invoice.policy_snapshot?.allow_override || false}
  isManager={userHasRole('Manager')}
  onSuccess={() => router.refresh()}  // Revalidate data
/>
```

**Shows Dynamic Buttons**:
- **Lock** (when OPEN)
- **Verify** (when LOCKED/VERIFIED, increments level)
- **Verify & Complete** (Manager only, if allow_override = true)
- **Unlock** (requires comment modal)
- **Unverify** (decrements level, requires comment)

#### 3. Lifecycle History (Audit Trail)
```tsx
import { LifecycleHistory } from "@/components/shared/LifecycleHistory";

<LifecycleHistory
  model="Invoice"
  instanceId={invoice.id}
/>
```

**Shows**: Timeline of all lifecycle actions with user, timestamp, comments, and metadata

